article.description: Katie Douglas scored 18 points, Asjha Jones had 16 points and nine rebounds and the Sun beat the Sky 74-56.
article.headline: Douglas, Jones lead Sun to third straight win
article.linkText: Douglas, Jones lead Sun to third straight win
article.story:
UNCASVILLE, Conn. -- Katie Douglas scored 18 points, Asjha Jones had 16 points and nine rebounds and the Connecticut Sun beat the Chicago Sky 74-56 on Tuesday night.

Evanthia Maltsi added 13 points for Connecticut and Lindsay Whalen had 10.

It was the third consecutive victory for the Sun (15-12), who went 9-2 in July.

Jia Perkins scored 17 points for Chicago (12-15), which had won four of five. Stacey Dales added 10 for the Sky.

Candice Dupree, who came in averaging almost 18 points for Chicago, was held to just four points by Jones, who shadowed her throughout the game.

The Sun jumped to a 24-14 lead after one quarter and stretched that to 33-16 early in the second. Chicago then went on an 11-0 run to get back into it.

Dupree's first points came on a pair of free throws with 2:41 left in the half and cut the deficit to 35-31. She made her only field goal on a fast break a minute later.

The Sun led 41-35 at the half and opened the second with an 11-2 run, led by Jones' six points. Connecticut was ahead 64-46 after three and coasted from there.

The teams had split their first two meetings of the season, with both teams winning on the road.
